AB  - Clean production is a new and creative paradigm that employs the environmental strategy of continuous overall prevention on the production process, products, and services. On the background of sustainable development, there is an urgent need for a method to quantitatively analyze the sustainability of a corporation's clean production. Emergy analysis theory explores a new perspective in the complex system of nature, the economy and society from all dimensions and develops a new method for quantitatively studying ecological systems, ecological economic systems and human activities. This method also provides a valid criterion for appraising sustainable development. In this paper, a longitudinal comparative study on the sustainability of the clean production of enterprise was conducted based on the emergy theory, using the example of Xinjiang Tianye Industrial Park, with the aim of identifying the development direction of the chloro-alkali industrial system from a sustainable perspective, and providing a scientific basis for stipulating appropriate management and control measures and development strategies. The results show that the clean production is the effective way of sustainable development of enterprise.
